Perfect! Now letâ€™s add a **Navbar** so users can navigate between pages like Home, Cart, Wishlist, Profile, etc.

---

## âœ… Step 4: Add Navbar Component

### ğŸ—‚ Create the file:

In `src/components/`, create a file named:

```
Navbar.tsx
```

---

### ğŸ§± Paste the following code into `Navbar.tsx`:

```tsx
import { Link, NavLink } from 'react-router-dom';
import './Navbar.css';

function Navbar() {
  return (
    <nav className="navbar">
      <div className="nav-left">
        <Link to="/" className="logo">
          #Hashdin by Deloitte
        </Link>
      </div>
      <div className="nav-right">
        <NavLink to="/" className="nav-link">Courses</NavLink>
        <NavLink to="/wishlist" className="nav-link">My Wishlist</NavLink>
        <NavLink to="/cart" className="nav-link">Cart</NavLink>
        <NavLink to="/profile" className="nav-link">My Profile</NavLink>
      </div>
    </nav>
  );
}

export default Navbar;
```

---

### ğŸ¨ Create Styling File

In the same `components` folder, create:

```
Navbar.css
```

And paste this styling to make it simple but nice:

```css
.navbar {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  background-color: #222;
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
  font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
}

.logo {
  color: #fff;
  font-weight: bold;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 1.2rem;
}

.nav-link {
  color: #ccc;
  text-decoration: none;
  margin-left: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

.nav-link:hover,
.nav-link.active {
  color: #f9d342;
}
```

---

### ğŸ”— Add Navbar to Your `App.tsx`

Update `App.tsx` to include `Navbar`:

```tsx
import { Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom';
import Home from './pages/Home';
import Cart from './pages/Cart';
import Wishlist from './pages/Wishlist';
import Profile from './pages/Profile';
import CourseDetails from './pages/CourseDetails';
import Navbar from './components/Navbar';

function App() {
  return (
    <>
      <Navbar />
      <div style={{ padding: '20px' }}>
        <Routes>
          <Route path="/" element={<Home />} />
          <Route path="/cart" element={<Cart />} />
          <Route path="/wishlist" element={<Wishlist />} />
          <Route path="/profile" element={<Profile />} />
          <Route path="/course/:id" element={<CourseDetails />} />
        </Routes>
      </div>
    </>
  );
}

export default App;
```

